gomodel:SYNGO_3980  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 1A and B show that endogenous VPS35 highly overlaps with VAMP2, indicating that VPS35 is localised to synapses. Fig1C-F show by immuno EM that VPS35 is predominantly localised to presynaptic terminals (quantification in Fig1D), but is not present in all presynaptic terminals (Fig1C) in line with the not-complete overlap observed in confocal studies (Fig 1A-B).\nInformation on Antibody validation:\nFig S2a: Negative control processed in parallel with the immunolabelling with\nVPS35 Cat. No. ab10099, but preincubating the primary antibody with the blocking peptide Cat. No. ab23181 at a ratio 5:1.\nFig S2b-c: Negative control processed in parallel with the immuno-gold labelling with VPS35, but without adding primary antibody, just bridging antibody and Protein A-gold.. Experimental description: Results \"We first characterized the distribution of retromer in mouse hippocampal synapses.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date           "2020-12-10" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3980" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

